text: Judith Pirchmoser (born 20 April 1968) is an Austrian taekwondo practitioner, and fitness instructor. She competed at the 1992 Summer Olympics, where taekwondo was a demonstration sport, in the lightweight event. At the European Taekwondo Championships she won the silver medal in 1990 and bronze medal in 1992 and 1994. == References == == Other websites == * JUDITH PIRCHMOSER Fitness Trainer Category:1968 births Category:Living people Category:Taekwondo practitioners Category:Austrian sportspeople
